statements.sql: select * from `users` where `id` = 1 and `users`.`deleted_at` is null limit 1

select `permissions`.*, `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` as `pivot_permission_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `permissions` inner join `model_has_permissions` on `permissions`.`id` = `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` where `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` = 'App\User'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\User'
select `name`, `color`, (select count(*) from `leads` where `lead_statuses`.`id` = `leads`.`lead_status_id` and `type` = 0 and `leads`.`deleted_at` is null) as `leads_count` from `lead_statuses`
select `status` from `meetings` where `meeting_id` is null and `meetings`.`deleted_at` is null

select `sales_id`, `tax`, `total_amount`, (select SUM(amount) as paid_amount from `contract_payments` where `lead_contracts`.`id` = `contract_payments`.`lead_contract_id`) as `paid_amount`, (select SUM(amount) as services_amount from `lead_contract_has_services` where `lead_contracts`.`id` = `lead_contract_has_services`.`lead_contract_id`) as `services_amount`, (select SUM(amount) as profit_company from `lead_contract_has_services` where `lead_contracts`.`id` = `lead_contract_has_services`.`lead_contract_id` and `profit_method` = 1) as `profit_company`, (select SUM(amount) as ads_amount from `lead_contract_has_services` where `lead_contracts`.`id` = `lead_contract_has_services`.`lead_contract_id` and `profit_method` = 0) as `ads_amount` from `lead_contracts` where `lead_contracts`.`deleted_at` is null
select count(*) as aggregate from `leads` where `type` = 0 and `leads`.`deleted_at` is null
select count(*) as aggregate from `leads` where `type` = 2 and `leads`.`deleted_at` is null
select count(*) as aggregate from `services` where `services`.`deleted_at` is null
